Title: Performing the Absolute. Marina Abramovic Organizing the Unfinished Business                 of Arthur Schopenhauer
Author-Name: Pierre Guillet de Monthoux
Abstract: Performance is a way of organising for value creation. The kind of value performance art aims to generate is neither use-nor exchange-value but aesthetic value, philosophically defined as searching for 'the absolute'. Philosophical asthetics, from Kant to Schopenhauer and Nietzsche, thus claims that art is the modem gateway to metaphysics. Pictures, texts and other artefacts are spin-offs of artists main function; performing the absolute. This paper illustrates this philosophical position by taking three practical examples which show how the artists Hans Makart, Herman Nitsch and Marina Abramovic three famous performance art managers - go about organizing the supply of an art to satisfy a demand for metaphysics.
Year: 1999
Volume: 20
Issue: 7
Keyword: symbolism, theatre, aesthetics, metaphysics, enactment
File-url: http://dx.doi.org/10.1177/017084060002000703
Journal: Organization Studies

