Title: Racing and Back-Pedalling into the Future: New Product Introduction and Organizational Mortality in the US Bicycle Industry, 1880-1918
Author-Name: Glen Dowell
Author-Name: Anand Swaminathan
Abstract: We hypothesize that some overlap of production between and within product generations reduces firm mortality, as it allows firms to retain valuable routines. Excessive overlap, however, becomes harmful. An analysis of the effects of new product introduction on mortality rates among the population of US bicycle producers over 1880-1918 supports our hypotheses. Our results suggest the value of separating out the content effects of innovation, which are often positive, from the process effects which tend to be disruptive.
Year: 2000
Volume: 21
Issue: 2
Keyword: product introduction, technological change, survival, organizational ecology
File-url: http://dx.doi.org/10.1177/0170840600212005
Journal: Organization Studies

